{
  "text": "On the other hand, GmSAL1, a soybean inositol 1-phosphatases, has been found to be involved in salt and drought response by the hydrolysis of inositol-1,4,5-trisphosphate (InsP 3 ) [CITATION_1] , suggesting the inositol signaling would also play a role in stress responses in soybean. The components including 5PTases, involved in inositol signaling, would be good candidates for soybean breeding of salt tolerance as well. However, the function of most 5PTases remains unknown in soybean.",
